"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The method `ax.set_xticks` expects the tick positions to be in the same units as the x-axis data, which in this case are dates. However, `df.date.unique()` returns an array of datetime objects, which may not be directly compatible with the tick positions expected by Matplotlib. Additionally, `ax.set_xticklabels` should be used with caution as it can lead to misalignment if the tick positions are not set correctly.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19c19\\n<ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n---\\n>ax.set_xticks([pd.to_datetime(d).toordinal() for d in df.date.unique()])\\n20c20\\n<ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n>ax.set_xticklabels(labels=[d.strftime('%Y-%m-%d') for d in df.date.unique()], rotation=45)\"\n}"